<br>
Randul, you are clearly making the confusion between totalitarianism and socialism.<br>
<br>
Those people who took power in USSR and China were a very tight minority in the galaxy of socialism, they totally perverted an ideology, in order to turn it in a convenient tool for themselves.<br>
<br>
No more, no less.<br>
<br>
The heart of socialism is very simple actually, its all about mankind: man must be the center of everything, it has to be the subject of his own future, not an object in a theory where welth creation would be the main concern (aka capitalism).<br>
<br>
Very simply, what are we talking about here?<br>
<br>
Social Justice, same Education for everyone, minimal housing and clothing guaranteed.<br>
<br>
Guarantee that everyone in the country will have the same access to those very basic needs, for the same price and at a very high quality : Energy, transports, education, Health system, Communications, ...<br>
<br>
This is called public utilities.<br>
<br>
The principles are easy to grasp: the private sphere must interfere the least possible, if you decide to work for your people, fine, but you will be at their service, the particularity beeing that you cant make benefits from such activity, nor demand any form of profitability except the general well beeing.<br>
<br>
It means of course that the state must be very strong, but why wouldnt it be the case, since its the manifestation of the Nation will?<br>
<br>
&quot;i dont want to merely exist and pay ungodly amounts of taxes and/or give my money away to others, i want to better my existance, have a better house, a better car a bette computer not just exist&quot;<br>
<br>
You just want to show off, but sadly that's an estate bellow existence.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;in my opinion the U.S.A needs to completely stop giving money to other contrys and spend it on the poor and sick in its own country&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
USA give less than 0,25 % of their gross national product to help development in the world.<br>
Maybe you think its too much when it should be at least 0,7% as US promised with the rest of OECD countries.<br>
<br>
In the meantime, 30000 people die everyday in the world because they dont have access to clean water.<br>
You see, i doubt they would give a @#%$ for your better computer.<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;oh and by the way, aids medicines are so expensive becuase they are hard to make and update, the damn disease is always adapting and changing so they neeed to keep changing the med, its not like medicine for the common cold, that can be used for many years without change, it has to be constantly updated,and upgraded&quot;<br>
<br>
Was it a reason to sue countries who decided to simply steal medics recipes, because they wouldnt be allowed to produce their own at low cost?<br>
In the meantime, whole countries are dying from AIDS.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Thats what happens when the most powerfull nation in the world is leaded by the heirs of some greedy british merchants who believed that God was walking at their sides.<br>
<br>
USA are not a nation. its the biggest lobby in the world, supported by its very well informed and courageous citizens =)<br>
<br>
Well, i dont totally believe what i just said about US citizens, i went to see &quot;Bowling for Columbine&quot; yesterday night, and man does it give a fresh feeling, it seems people are starting to wake up =)<br>
<br>
-Belarkan.<br>
